ProtoDefines:
. "An $n$th root of unity is a complex number $\zeta$ such 
   that $\zeta^n=1$. A root of unity $\zeta$ is a primitive 
   $n$th root of unity if $n$ is the smallest positive integer 
   such that $\zeta^n=1$."
